item.title: Global stocks, oil up despite virus surge
item.description: Markets have showed signs of optimism, with European shares opening higher and oil prices rising despite a record number of new COVID-19 infections in the United States.

item.title: Iran explosion caused by tank leak: TV
item.description: An explosion at an Iranian gas storage facility close to a sensitive military site near Tehran was caused by a tank leak, a defence ministry spokesman has told state TV.

item.title: Myanmar burns over $1b worth of drugs
item.description: More than $US839 million ($A1.2 billion) worth of seized illegal drugs have been destroyed in Myanmar to mark the annual International Day against Drug Abuse and Illicit Trafficking.

item.title: Man’s body found near Melbourne school
item.description: A body has been found near a school in Melbourne's southeast, sparking a homicide squad investigation.

item.title: ‘Berserk’ numbers of ill on Ruby Princess
item.description: A Carnival Australia executive says he was unaware the ill-fated Ruby Princess cruise ship was low on medical supplies and swabs or that the number of ill passengers had gone "berserk".

item.title: Virus hardens grip, especially in US
item.description: While China moves closer to containing a fresh outbreak in Beijing, the coronavirus has taken a stronger hold in many countries, particularly the United States.

item.title: S.Korean police raid activist’s office
item.description: South Korean police have raided the office of an activist whose anti-North Korea leafleting campaign has intensified tensions on the Korean Peninsula.

item.title: No action on lobbyist register integrity
item.description: The federal attorney-general's department failed to take action on changes to improve the way lobbyists are regulated, a new report has found.

item.title: Trump asks Supreme Court to axe Obamacare
item.description: The Trump administration has asked the US Supreme Court to invalidate the law dubbed Obamacare that, introduced by predecessor, added millions of Americans to the country's healthcare safety net.

item.title: Qld cafe explosion motorist unfit to drive
item.description: The man who crashed his ute into a Queensland cafe, sparking an explosion that killed two people and seriously injured more than a dozen others, should not have been behind the wheel, a coroner says.
